title: For Sale:  Early "C" Yugoslavian SKS PAP M59 5-digit
postcontent:
Thank you for looking.

For sale today, we have a very early Yugoslavian SKS PAP M59 rifle.  This is a 5-digit C-serial model, C-41786.  That puts it at almost the beginning of the Yugoslavian SKS dates.  http://www.sksboards.com/smf/index.php?topic=81.0

The configuration of this rifle is a standard setup with blade bayonet, no grenade launcher, and standard length.  The stock has minor marks, as seen in the pictures, but it doesn't appear to have any major damage to it at all.  The serial numbers are stamped and electro-penciled.  I didn't find any arsenal marks at all, which is in-line with it being a very early Yugoslavian SKS.  The barrel looks excellent.  This model should not be chrome-lined, but the bore and crown are extremely clean, making it look chromed.

(Note about chroming: Chrome-plating protects bores from corrosion, which was a concern with old ammo.  It also protected against oxidation.  However, early chroming was generally uneven, leading to a reduction in accuracy.  This bore is clean and non-chromed, meaning that you can shoot new non-corrosive ammo and clean it as normal, and it should provide outstanding accuracy.)

Internally, it doesn't seem to have much wear at all.  I doubt it saw any action at all, and it doesn't seem to have been abused by any prior owner.  Because I believed this to be a good example rifle, I didn't modify it in any way.

The rifle is as shown in the pictures, and it does not include the cleaning kit, but it does include the rod.  I have torn this rifle down and not found any conflicting serial numbers.

I'm asking $550 (Edit: Lowered to $499.)  I am willing to ship to your FFL for an additional fee.  Thank you again for looking.  If you have any questions or comments, please feel free to ask.

(Additional photos are available upon request.)

title: For Sale:  Fun Shooting Competition Saturday May 2nd!!!
postcontent:
Ok shooters, get your gear ready!  We have another run and gun event coming up soon!  Many of you know who we are, but here is our website for the newcomers out there: http://rac-frag.weebly.com/

Here is a video of me running one of the courses we set up last summer. This will give you an idea of the type of shooting we are doing.    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uDcMGPO6uKM

We are RAC FRAG- Responsible Armed Citzens, and this is Fun Run And Gun.  We offer a fun and unique experience to allow you to train with your weapons in a way that many of you are not able to do.  We set up a course that involves engaging multiple targets at different shooting stations.  You are required to run from station to station with your rifle and hit targets at ranges of 20 yards to about 150 yards, with a few handgun targets along the way.  

So come out and join us for a day of shooting fun!  We are a great bunch of guys to hang out with. Please don't be shy.  None of us are professional competition shooters. We just enjoy shooting guns and practicing.  All skill levels are welcome to our events.  Even my dear old dad hobbles through the course with us at 60 plus years old, so it really is for everybody. It is just plain fun all around, plus you get good training that you could never get at an indoor range. We also have a plate rack and a dueling tree for people to entertain themselves with while they aren't running our course. We will have a grill on site if you want to bring some meat to toss on it for lunch.  We will also have an outhouse on site.

You can register for our events on our website.  Please feel free to call or text me if you have any questions.  I don't live on my computer so I may not respond to emails promptly. Thanks for reading!  Cody REDACTED

title: For Sale:  50-round NATO .308 Ball, M80, MilSpec
postcontent:
Only FOUR bags left!  Bags of 50 rounds of this military-specification 150-gr ammo used for all NATO troops. This is India manufacture and shoots very consistently and clean. I used this to get a general sight-in with my bolt-action hunting rifle and to practice.

Price is for one bag. I have FOUR bags remaining. I won't ship this stuff - too expensive because it must go ground.

If you are brave and have a lot of patience you can try reloading this ammo as well. The brass is very strong but they are Berdan primed and you have to drill the military-style primer out from inside the case to create a flash hole (Berdan primed brass does not have a conventional flash hole) and then either drill out the primer from the outside (carefully) or use a punch from inside the case, one at a time. A boxer deprimer pin from a 2- or 3-die set will not do the job.
